The paper deals with the difficulty of counting nodes in a synchronous dynamic network, which involves topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of broadcast communication and network topology changes also suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT). The focus on anonymity in the title and abstract may suggest a connection to security and privacy (cs.SI).
